===Noun===
{{en-plural noun|[[you]] [[people]]}}

# {{pejorative}} any outsiders of a [[clique]]
# Members of a particular group, collectively.
#: ''That is the type of thing '''you people''' would say.''

====Usage notes====
* In the United States, this expression, however intended, by the speaker, has been interpreted as indicative of racism when used in discourse with those of a race different from the speakers, or of discrimination on and ethnic or religious basis in analogous situations.

